{
  "texts": [
    "Tasks such as multi-turn financial question answering (CONVFINQA) and advanced causal classification require lengthy incontext prompts, leading to high inference costs.",
    "Notably, smaller models sometimes outperform larger ones by offering a superior trade-off between throughput and accuracy, making them more viable for real-world applications.",
    "For all of our inference runs, DeepSeek R1 cost approximately $260 USD compared to Claude 3.5 Sonnet's and o1-mini's $105 USD and Meta Llama 3.1 8b's $4 USD.",
    "This dramatic price difference suggests that users should choose models carefully based on use-case, as slightly lower performing models might have dramatically cheaper inference costs.",
    "For example, models such as Llama 3.1 70b and DeepSeek-V3 cost less than $25 USD."
  ]
}